{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17-251-now-playing-and-remote-commands-on-tvos"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video and providing notes! It’s super easy:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Related Sessions","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Related-Sessions"},{"items":["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-209-Whats-New-in-tvOS","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-206-Whats-New-in-tvOS","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-503-Advances-in-AVFoundation-Playback","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-506-AVKit-on-tvOS"],"type":"links","style":"list"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-251-Now-Playing-and-Remote-Commands-on-tvOS","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2017\/251","type":"reference","overridingTitle":"Watch Video (14 min)"}},"kind":"article","sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17"]]},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"WWDC17","role":"sampleCode","title":"Now Playing and Remote Commands on tvOS","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}]},"abstract":[{"text":"Consistent and intuitive control of media playback is key to many apps on tvOS, and proper use and configuration of MPNowPlayingInfoCenter and MPRemoteCommandCenter are critical to delivering a great user experience. Dive deeper into these frameworks and learn how to ensure a seamless experience whether your app is being controlled using Siri, the Siri Remote, or the iOS Remote app.","type":"text"}],"references":{"https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2017/251":{"type":"download","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2017\/251","checksum":null,"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2017\/251"},"WWDC17-Icon.png":{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC17-Icon.png","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-Icon.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"alt":null},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16-506-AVKit-on-tvOS":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-506-avkit-on-tvos","role":"sampleCode","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-506-AVKit-on-tvOS","title":"AVKit on tvOS","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"AVKit on tvOS offers an intuitive user interface for interaction with your media on this powerful new platform. AVKit is built on AVFoundation, which gives you access to the full potential of platform services for operating on time-based audiovisual media. Learn how to leverage the new content proposal APIs, and how to create a seamless interstitial playback experience. Management of media metadata and chapter navigation will also be covered."}],"type":"topic"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16-206-Whats-New-in-tvOS":{"title":"What’s New in tvOS","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-206-Whats-New-in-tvOS","type":"topic","kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Apps are quickly changing how we experience TV today, and tvOS is the foundation upon which new apps and ideas are being built. Take your app to the next level with great new features in tvOS 10. Learn all about the new interface appearance APIs, support for badging and notifications, and more.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-206-whats-new-in-tvos","role":"sampleCode"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC17":{"title":"WWDC17","type":"topic","role":"collectionGroup","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Xcode 9, Swift 4.0, iOS 11, macOS 10.13 (High Sierra), tvOS 11, watchOS 4."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"New APIs: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Core NFC"},{"type":"text","text":" and more."}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDC17-Icon.png"},{"type":"card","identifier":"WWDC17.jpeg"}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC17-209-Whats-New-in-tvOS":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-209-Whats-New-in-tvOS","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"tvOS allows you to deliver incredible apps and games for the big screen with the tvOS SDK. Gain insights into new tvOS 11 capabilities and enhancements such as Right-to-Left support, image overlays, background app updates, and user interface style improvements. And with the new AVKit capabilities you can take your media playback experience even further."}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17-209-whats-new-in-tvos","title":"What’s New in tvOS","type":"topic","kind":"article","role":"sampleCode"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16-503-Advances-in-AVFoundation-Playback":{"kind":"article","role":"sampleCode","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-503-Advances-in-AVFoundation-Playback","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"AVFoundation is a powerful framework for media operations, providing capture, editing, playback, and export. Learn about new APIs and methods for media playback. Create seamless loops, simplify your playback logic with “autowait”, and see how to deliver an even faster playback startup experience."}],"title":"Advances in AVFoundation Playback","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-503-advances-in-avfoundation-playback"},"WWDC17.jpeg":{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC17.jpeg","alt":null,"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17.jpeg"}]},"WWDCNotes.png":{"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","type":"image","alt":null,"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"type":"link","title":"Learn More…","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn More…"}],"url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"role":"collection","images":[{"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","type":"icon"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community."}],"type":"topic","title":"WWDC Notes","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes"}}}